		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Default [1.50]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>You guys are all wrong.&nbsp;&nbsp;Why do you hotkey so many spells?  I also didnt see many /pet back off hotkeys, what do you do if your pet starts chasing something?  These are the hotkeys i use at lvl 45.<br><br>1, /pet attack<br>2, Spells (Brings you to spellbook for quick change of spells)<br>3, Sit (allows you to med during battles and keep an eye on what you are fighting)<br>4, Persona (Just a basic utility, can use the "i" key but i choose not to)<br>5, /pet back off (a out of control pet makes you unwanted in groups and messes up screaming terror)<br>6, Jboots (all necros should have them, i dont see how you can solo anything without them, they are hotkeyed for easy access incase they start to wear off during a fight)<br><br>I dont keep any spells hotkeyed because they are easily clicked on with the pointer and you wont save any time using keys.<br><br>Tiviz Contagion<br>Lvl 45 necro on luclin</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >1 Replies</td></tr></table>
